2. Complete User Flows
2.1 New Farmer Onboarding Flow
1. Downloads APK from WhatsApp link or QR code
2. Opens app → Splash checks Supabase session → No session → Login screen
3. Enters 10-digit mobile number → taps 'Send OTP →'
4. Supabase sends SMS OTP → OTP screen shows masked number
5. Enters 6-digit OTP → 'Verify & Continue →'
6. New user detected (no farm record) → STEP 2 of 3: Create Farm
7. Enters Farm Name + Location → 'Create Farm →'
8. STEP 3 of 3: Create Pond — name, size (acres), stocking date, PL count, num trays
9. Taps 'Save Pond & Generate Feed Plan →'
10.System writes: farms row, ponds row, stockings row, 30× feed_plans rows (DOC 1–30)
11.Redirects to Tank Page for new pond — Blind Feed Mode (DOC 1–15 if stocked today)
2.2 Daily Feed Logging Flow (DOC 1–15: Blind Mode)
12.Opens app → Splash detects session → Farm Dashboard
13.Taps 'Tanks' tab → sees pond tabs, selects Pond 1
14.Sees TODAY'S PROGRESS bar + BLIND PLAN BASED badge
15.Current round card highlighted (amber border, NOW badge)
16.Taps 'MARK AS FED' → system logs feed_log row with is_blind=true, tray_multiplier=1.0
17.Round marked DONE (green) → progress bar advances
18.Repeat for all 6 rounds across the day
2.3 Daily Feed Logging Flow (DOC 16+: Tray Feed Mode)
19.Opens app → Tank Page → TRAY FEED MODE badge shown
20.Current round shows recommended feed quantity (tray-adjusted from previous check)
21.Taps 'MARK AS FED' → round logged → app prompts: 'Log Tray Check for this round?'
22.Tray Check screen: shows Tray 1 of 4 — farmer picks status (Empty/Small/Half/Full)
23.If applicable: select observations (Dead shrimp, Red legs, etc.)
24.Taps 'Save' → moves to Tray 2 of 4 → saves → Tray 3 → Tray 4
25.System computes weighted avg multiplier → stores in tray_checks
26.Next round card updates: shows NEW quantity + AUTO ADJUSTED blue badge
27.If supplement due: SUPPLEMENT REQUIRED card shows in next round
2.4 Sampling Flow
28.'Due in 2d' badge shows on Sampling icon (DOC > 30, last sample > 10 days ago)
29.Taps Sampling → Growth Monitoring screen
30.Enters Sample Count (e.g. 100 shrimp) + Total Weight (e.g. 350g)
